The Telegraph - Calcutta
 CABs unique plan for umpires
 BY A STAFF REPORTER  Calcutta:After the players,  its the umpires. The CAB has decided to impart motivational  training to the local umpires in a seminar organised by  the state association on October 25. Its the same agency which will do the motivation training for the senior and under-19 Bengal players. The company does similar training with multinational executives. They gave a demonstration to the different age-group coaches and it was very well received, a senior CAB official informed. Senior Mumbai and Bengal umpires M.R. Singh and Subrata Banerjee will conduct the seminar. However, the state umpires demand for a pay hike has been ruled out.  Bangla exchange tour  The Bangladesh under-15 team will  arrive in the city on October 7 to play a series of matches  with their Bengal counterparts. They will play two two-day,  one three-day and two one-day matches. One of the matches  will be played in Kalyani, which the CAB is mooting as an  alternative venue.  Copyright 
